While a fixed fibre connection is the ideal tether to the Internet, this is not always a viable option. Users who travel a lot and those without fixed broadband coverage instead have to resort to LTE connections, which can be expensive and less than reliable. If you use a SIM and LTE data package which offers good value for your money, however, you can get decent usage and speeds out of the connection. Power users who need fast speeds for multiple devices while on the move or at home can be served by a powerful mobile hotspot, which has many useful features. An LTE data connection, SD card support, and power bank functionality can all be packed into the mobile device. Some of these devices also offer impressive network capabilities, including dual-band Wi-Fi and support for up to 32 connected devices. We rounded up some of the best mobile Wi-Fi hotspots available in South Africa, according to their specifications, and listed them below.     